    "body": "This PR generally reworks the 2:4 sparse CUTLASS kernels, cleaning up the implementation, and fixes several issues.\n\n* `cutlass_sparse_compress` and `cutlass_scaled_sparse_mm` now share the dispatching for hyperparameter selection. This lets the compressor derive the sparse format from the GEMM kernel. Now the sparse format has a single source of truth and it lets us pare down the code size for `cutlass_sparse_compress`.\n* `cutlass_sparse_compress` now allocates and returns `a_nzs` and `a_meta`. Necessary because `cutlass_sparse_compress` requires padding in some cases (e.g. where the K dimension is not a multiple of 128).\n* Fixes an IMA and/or garbage output when `bias is not None`. `cutlass_scaled_sparse_mm` internally transposes the operation, which means the bias is a column vector instead of a row vector.  Added a separate epilogue for that case. (this happened in the qkv_proj in `nm-testing/Qwen2.5-0.5B-sparse2of4_fp8_dynamic-e2e`)\n* Fixes an issue where float16 or bfloat16 2:4 models where zero entries were stored as `-0.0` would produce garbage output (`nm-testing/llama-2-7b-sparse2of4`).\n\n**Note**: With this PR I updated the kernels so that bfloat16 and float16 `cutlass_scaled_sparse_mm` GEMMs must have the same output dtype as their input operands. Purely for binary size/compile time reasons. Easy to add back in if anyone has an objection.\n",
    "created_at": "2025-02-13T03:42:53Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-02-14T00:01:15Z",
